---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How StackVerdict handles analytics and the optional email you can leave for the deep-dive report."
  canonical="https://stackverdict.dev/privacy"
>
  <article class="wrap prose section-top">
    <nav class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / Privacy Policy</nav>

    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Draft — not legal advice.</strong> This is a placeholder written to describe what
      the site actually does today. Have it reviewed by a lawyer before treating it as your
      real privacy policy.
    </div>

    <h2>Who runs this site</h2>
    <p>
      StackVerdict (stackverdict.dev) is operated by [your name / company, address, contact email].
      This section needs your real legal details before this page is real.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      We use <a href="https://plausible.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Plausible Analytics</a>
      to understand how the site is used — for example, how many people start and finish the
      cost calculator. Plausible is cookie-free and does not collect or store any personal data
      or cross-site identifiers. It only reports aggregated numbers (page views and the named
      events below); no individual visitor is tracked or identifiable. Because no cookies and no
      personal data are involved, no consent banner is shown or required for this analytics.
    </p>
    <p>We track the following named events inside the calculator:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>calculator_started</code> — you began the calculator.</li>
      <li><code>calculator_completed</code> — you reached a result.</li>
      <li><code>email_submitted</code> — you submitted the optional email form below the results.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The email field on the results page</h2>
    <p>
      Below your calculator results, you can optionally leave your email address to be notified
      when a deeper, paid report (your optimal model mix per task, and your break-even threshold)
      becomes available. This feature does not exist yet — submitting your email only registers
      your interest.
    </p>
    <p>
      Submitting this form is entirely optional and requires an explicit, unchecked opt-in
      checkbox. If you submit it, your email address is sent to [form processor — e.g. Formspree]
      for us to store and later contact you. It is used only to notify you about this report and
      is not sold, shared with third parties for marketing, or used for any other purpose. We
      don't store it in your browser (no localStorage) or put it in a URL.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      If you've submitted your email, you can ask us to tell you what we hold, correct it, or
      delete it at any time by contacting [contact email]. Since analytics has no personal data
      tied to it, there's nothing individual to access or delete there.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      This is an early, draft version of this page. It will be updated as the site and its data
      practices evolve.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
